==English==
=== Etymology ===
From Latin ''[[verbum]]'', word

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /vɜːrˈbeɪtɪm/
*[[SAMPA]]: /<tt>v3:r'beItIm</tt>/

===Adverb===
'''verbatim'''
#In the [[exact]] same [[word]]s (as were used originally).
#:''Give the speech '''verbatim''', in the manner of President Lincoln.''

====Synonyms====
*[[word for word]]

===Adjective===
'''verbatim''' (''no [[comparative]] or [[superlative]]'')

#Of a document, [[corresponding]] with the [[original]] [[word for word]].
#:''I have copied his speech and here it is, '''verbatim'''.''
#Of a person, [[able]] to take down a [[speech]] word for word, especially in [[shorthand]].

====Synonyms====
*(''document''): [[word for word]]

===Noun===
'''verbatim''' (''plural'' '''verbatims''')

#A word-for-word [[report]] of a speech.

